title: Philippe de Gaulle, naval commander and son of French leader, dies at 102
description: He fought for France in World War II under his father’s command, and became a caretaker of Gen. Charles de Gaulle’s legacy after his death.

title: For Putin’s election in occupied Ukraine, voting is forced at gunpoint
description: Russian soldiers are pressuring people to vote in occupied Ukraine as Vladimir Putin seeks to cement his illegal annexations and create a facade of legitimacy.

title: The U.S. has tried to ‘fix’ Haiti before. How will this time be different?
description: History weighs on the Biden administration as it seeks to bring stability to Haiti. Critics say officials are at risk of repeating past mistakes.

title: Crisis in Haiti comes after decades of turmoil: A chronology
description: Here’s a timeline of key events in Haiti’s modern political history, leading up to the ongoing crisis.

title: U.S. attempts to stop arms smuggling to Yemen with limited resources
description: The U.S. intelligence community, Special Operations forces and other U.S. troops have mounted an expanded effort to squelch weapons deliveries to the Houthis.

title: In this Ukrainian village, almost no men are left
description: With Ukraine’s military badly outnumbered by the invading Russians and desperately in need of more soldiers, villages like Makiv are being emptied of their fighting-age men.

title: Netanyahu approves plans for Israeli military operation in Rafah
description: Humanitarian groups and several world leaders have warned that an invasion of the densely populated Gazan city could be disastrous for those seeking refuge there.

title: Thousands of Gazans have gone missing. No one is accounting for them.
description: Many disappeared under the rubble after airstrikes. Others are believed to have been detained at Israeli checkpoints. Some simply left one day and never returned.
